parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The protruding exhaust pipes can cause skin burns to the lower extremities of passengers, especially when unloading items from the trunk.
symptoms: Exhaust pipes protrude out and are extremely hot after the engine is turned off
passengers are at risk of skin burns when leaning into the trunk area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Metal contamination in the fuel system can cause the engine to stall or shut off unexpectedly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
metal debris is found in the fuel system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical steering column component can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or unresponsive, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the TPS (Traction Control System) light illuminates
and the rear tailgate screen fails to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic jack saddle can cause the vehicle to collapse while being lifted, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential injury to the person lifting it.
symptoms: The jack saddle breaks or dislodges from the vehicle
causing the vehicle to fall suddenly
and resulting in damage to the rocker panel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Worn or failed motor mounts can cause excessive engine movement, leading to premature wear on other engine components, decreased vehicle performance, and potentially causing the engine to stall or fail, which can increase the risk of accidents.

The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof glass can cause a loud noise, startling the driver and potentially leading to loss of control of the vehicle. Additionally, shattered glass can fall onto the driver and passengers, causing injury.
symptoms: sudden shattering of the sunroof glass
glass fragments falling onto the driver and passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fractured fuel line can cause fuel to leak onto the exhaust manifold, leading to a fire hazard, engine stall, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Gas odor coming from the vehicle
